@startuml
title Workflow with LLM Cache (Code inspection example)

actor User
participant "LLM (by gptel)" as LLM
participant "Emacs (llm-cache)" as Cache

activate LLM

User -> LLM: "Please, inspect functions caled 'gptel-send' and 'gptel-request'.\nI want a summary of the most relevant factors for the flow of a query."

LLM -> LLM: I want inspect and keep multiple relevant\ntags for final analisis.

LLM -> Cache: llm_cache_set("relevant-tags", "'()")
activate Cache
Cache --> LLM: success
deactivate Cache

LLM ->> User: investigate_code_tag("gptel-send")
note right: LLM uses investigate tools

User -->> LLM: ('gptel-send'tag content)
LLM -> LLM: Inspect the content and think is relevant.

LLM -> Cache: llm_cache_set("relevant-tags", "'(\"gptel-send sanitized code...\")")
activate Cache
Cache --> LLM: success
deactivate Cache

LLM ->> User: investigate_code_tag("gptel-request")
note right: LLM uses tools again

User -->> LLM: ('gptel-request'tag content)
LLM -> LLM: inspect and thik is relevant.

LLM -> Cache: llm_cache_get("relevant-tags")
activate Cache
Cache --> LLM: "'(\"gptel-send sanitized code...\")"
deactivate Cache

LLM -> LLM: Merge the result with a new tag.

LLM -> Cache: llm_cache_set("relevant-tags", "'(\"gptel-send code...\" \"gptel-request code...\")")
activate Cache
Cache --> LLM: success
deactivate Cache

LLM -> LLM: Now I have all important code.\nI can generate the final answer.

LLM -> Cache: llm_cache_get("relevant-tags")
activate Cache
Cache --> LLM: (Returns the complete list of relevant tags)
deactivate Cache

LLM -> User: "Based on the functions investigated, the main flow is...\n[Detailed and cohesive summary]"

deactivate LLM

@enduml
